# Privilege Escalation

## Overview
In this step, I simulated an attempt to gain elevated privileges after initial access.

## Attack Execution

runas /user:Administrator cmd

## Detection in Wazuh
Relevant logs:
- Event ID 4672 – Special privileges assigned

## Analysis
This event indicates that an account received elevated rights.

On its own, it might be normal. Combined with earlier activity, it becomes highly suspicious.

## MITRE ATT&CK
T1068 – Privilege Escalation

## Takeaway
Privilege changes should always be reviewed in context. They are rarely isolated events.
